  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >OVR Locomotion Effect is an overlay tool that aims to reduce VR (motion) sickness. It displays comfortable effect to HMD with thumb-stick input. You can use the effect to all SteamVR games.  </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Free Demo</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>We recommend trying the demo first before making your purchase.</strong> It is a fully featured, but time-limited for each try. It should be compatible with any VR game in your library. See if it helps reduce VR sickness for you. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Anti-VR sickness effect with thumb-stick inputs</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/3f0b516797efe30f88181e1017f38c27.poster.avif?t=1757680865\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/3f0b516797efe30f88181e1017f38c27.webm?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/3f0b516797efe30f88181e1017f38c27.mp4?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Displays VR-sickness reducing effect on the HMD based on your control inputs. After initial setup, the effect may be applied to any SteamVR game.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Dashboard settings</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/c0d140b00c055eb3597db14efc4c9839.poster.avif?t=1757680865\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/c0d140b00c055eb3597db14efc4c9839.webm?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/c0d140b00c055eb3597db14efc4c9839.mp4?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Quickly adjust effects on the SteamVR dashboard. </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Various effects</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/6cf3421c35519ad2f8401fbcc9093870.poster.avif?t=1757680865\" width=600 height=226 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/6cf3421c35519ad2f8401fbcc9093870.webm?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/6cf3421c35519ad2f8401fbcc9093870.mp4?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >There are vignette, room, point and wind effects. These effects can be combined use. You can adjust it to be barely visible or cover a large portion of the field of view. </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Gamepad</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/7c2b4ce69f402f25da0fd655c9d333ca.poster.avif?t=1757680865\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/7c2b4ce69f402f25da0fd655c9d333ca.webm?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/7c2b4ce69f402f25da0fd655c9d333ca.mp4?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Gamepad supported. Get rid of the sickness from your VR mods. </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >User guide, FAQ, Bug reports and requests</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Please check the forum (discussion) page from right menu of this page. You can get support from the forum or discord server.</p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >OVR Locomotion Effect is an overlay tool that aims to reduce VR (motion) sickness. It displays comfortable effect to HMD with thumb-stick input. You can use the effect to all SteamVR games.  </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Free Demo</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>We recommend trying the demo first before making your purchase.</strong> It is a fully featured, but time-limited for each try. It should be compatible with any VR game in your library. See if it helps reduce VR sickness for you. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Anti-VR sickness effect with thumb-stick inputs</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/3f0b516797efe30f88181e1017f38c27.poster.avif?t=1757680865\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/3f0b516797efe30f88181e1017f38c27.webm?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/3f0b516797efe30f88181e1017f38c27.mp4?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Displays VR-sickness reducing effect on the HMD based on your control inputs. After initial setup, the effect may be applied to any SteamVR game.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Dashboard settings</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/c0d140b00c055eb3597db14efc4c9839.poster.avif?t=1757680865\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/c0d140b00c055eb3597db14efc4c9839.webm?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/c0d140b00c055eb3597db14efc4c9839.mp4?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Quickly adjust effects on the SteamVR dashboard. </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Various effects</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/6cf3421c35519ad2f8401fbcc9093870.poster.avif?t=1757680865\" width=600 height=226 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/6cf3421c35519ad2f8401fbcc9093870.webm?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/6cf3421c35519ad2f8401fbcc9093870.mp4?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >There are vignette, room, point and wind effects. These effects can be combined use. You can adjust it to be barely visible or cover a large portion of the field of view. </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Gamepad</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/7c2b4ce69f402f25da0fd655c9d333ca.poster.avif?t=1757680865\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/7c2b4ce69f402f25da0fd655c9d333ca.webm?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1393780/extras/7c2b4ce69f402f25da0fd655c9d333ca.mp4?t=1757680865\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Gamepad supported. Get rid of the sickness from your VR mods. </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >User guide, FAQ, Bug reports and requests</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Please check the forum (discussion) page from right menu of this page. You can get support from the forum or discord server.</p>",
